Thirdly, in leading a man in the way of penance and bringing again, and this is signified in Tobit, in the fifth chapter, in the angel that led him and brought him again. The second profit that the angel doth, is that he tall not into sin, and this doth the angel in three manners. First, in letting the evil to be done, that it be not done, and this is signified in the book of Numbers in the twenty-second chapter. For Balaam, which went for to curse Israel, was let of the angel. Secondly, in blaming the sin past, that man depart from it, and that is signified in the book of Judges in the second chapter, how the angels blamed the children of Israel for break- ing of the law, wherefor they wept. Thirdly, in bringing strength for to take away the sin present, and this is signified in Lot, when he was led out by force, he, his wife, and his daughters, from the city of Sodom, that is to wit, from the customance of sin.
